411 other interested parties regarding privacy issues associated with the disclosure of
422 motor vehicle data.
3 D. By January 15, 2026, and annually thereafter, the commission shall submit to the
4 Governor, the Attorney General and the joint standing committee of the Legislature
5 having jurisdiction over business matters a report outlining the commission's activities
6 during the preceding year, describing any implementation or compliance issues relating
7 to this section that the commission identified and recommending any changes to this
8 section to address implementation, compliance or other identified issues. After
9 reviewing the report, the joint standing committee may report out legislation relating
10 to the report.'
