16 'Sec. 7. 29-A MRSA §1810, sub-§6, as enacted by IB 2023, c. 3, §3, is repealed.
17 Sec. 8. 29-A MRSA §1810, sub-§6-A is enacted to read:
18 6-A. Telematics system; diagnostic and repair function. Not later than 24 months
19 after the effective date of this subsection, a manufacturer that enables its dealers or
20 designated motor vehicle repair facilities in the State to perform a diagnostic and repair
21 function on the manufacturer's motor vehicles sold in the State that use a telematics system
22 shall make available, on fair and reasonable terms, to an owner of the manufacturer's motor
23 vehicle that uses a telematics system or to an owner-authorized independent repair facility
24 of the owner's choosing the means to perform the diagnostic and repair function on the
25 motor vehicle in a manner commensurate to that offered by the manufacturer to its dealers
26 and designated motor vehicle repair facilities in the State, which must include the capability
27 to remotely perform the diagnostic and repair function if the manufacturer enables its
28 dealers and designated motor vehicle repair facilities in the State to remotely perform that
29 function.
30 Sec. 9. 29-A MRSA §1810, sub-§8, as enacted by IB 2023, c. 3, §3, is repealed
31 and the following enacted in its place:
32 8. Enforcement; civil action. If the commission has reason to believe that a
33 manufacturer has violated any provision of this section, the commission shall notify the
34 Attorney General of that potential violation. In response to such a referral from the
35 commission, or in any other instance in which the Attorney General has reason to believe
36 that a manufacturer has violated any provision of this section, the Attorney General may
37 institute an action in the Superior Court of any county of the State to enforce the
38 requirements of this section. The Attorney General may seek injunctive relief and a civil
39 penalty of not more than $10,000 for each violation of this section.
40 An owner or owner-authorized independent repair facility that has been denied access by a
41 manufacturer to mechanical data in violation of this section may initiate a civil action
42 seeking any remedies under law. Each denial of access to an owner or owner-authorized
