413 independent repair facility is compensable by an award of treble damages or $10,000,
424 whichever amount is greater.'
3 Amend the bill by inserting after section 9 the following:
4 'Sec. 10. Staggered terms. Notwithstanding the Maine Revised Statutes, Title
5 29-A, section 1810, subsection 2-A, paragraph B, of the members initially appointed to the
6 Motor Vehicle Right to Repair Commission, 4 members must be appointed to an initial
7 term of one year, 4 members must be appointed to an initial term of 2 years and 4 members
8 must be appointed to an initial term of 3 years. '
9 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
10 number to read consecutively.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, changes the title of the
1133 bill. It amends the automotive right to repair law by repealing the provisions of that law
1144 that established an independent entity and instead establishes the Motor Vehicle Right to
1155 Repair Commission, which is charged with, among other things, monitoring and assessing
1166 implementation of and manufacturers' compliance with the requirements of that law. The
1177 amendment also makes other clarifying changes to the automotive right to repair law,
1188 including changes regarding the required equipment under that law, access to diagnostic
1199 and repair functions and enforcement of the law.
